fpzip
------------------------------------------
fpzip is a BSD licensed open source library for lossless or lossy compression
of large multidimensional floating-point arrays. Although written in C++,
fpzip has a C interface.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libfpzip-devel-1.3.0-1bl2
  libfpzip1-1.3.0-1bl2
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/LLNL/fpzip

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/LLNL/fpzip/archive/refs/tags/1.3.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack fpzip-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./fpzip-1.3.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/fpzip-1.3.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/fpzip-1.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfpzip1-1.3.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libfpzip-devel-1.3.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(fpzip)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/fpzip.README
  /usr/share/doc/fpzip/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/fpzip/NOTICE
  /usr/share/doc/fpzip/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/fpzip/VERSIONS.md

(libfpzip1)
  /usr/bin/cygfpzip-1.dll

(libfpzip-devel)
  /usr/include/fpzip.h
  /usr/lib/cmake/fpzip/fpzip-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/fpzip/fpzip-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/fpzip/fpzip-targets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/fpzip/fpzip-targets.cmake
  /usr/lib/libfpzip.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/fpzip.pc

